observations.recommendation:
We have recommended that:

The 20% development fund should be appropriated and utilized for programs and projects that are considered capital or investment in nature; 
Henceforth, management should strictly observe the pertinent provisions of DILG-DBM Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2011-1 dated April 13, 2011 on the appropriation and utilization of the 20% of the annual IRA for development

We have recommended the following:

The Municipal Mayor creates a GFPS Execom, TWG and Secretariat that will supervise, advocate and install a GAD Focal Point System (GFPS) as well as the required Gender Responsive Monitoring and Evaluation (M&E) System;
 The Municipal Mayor with the help of the Sangguniang Bayan, formulate and adapt a Local GAD Code;
The MSWDO being the leading authority in identifying gender related issues and concerns, see to it that GAD activities are identified through the use of HGDG and that the GAD plan are regularly updated; and
Henceforth, management sees to it that said plan and budget are approved by the DILG and the PPDO.

We have recommended the following:
The Municipal Treasurer should be granted only cash advances for payroll, honoraria and petty operating  expenses;
Payments out of cash advance should not exceed ₱15,000.00 and purchase of goods, repair and maintenance of vehicles and payment of terminal leave benefits should be paid directly thru checks;
A petty cash fund should be maintained for payment of expenses not exceeding ₱1,000.00 and claims above ₱1,000 should be paid through check as provided under Paragraph 3, Item IX, Section 83 of the Local Treasury Manual;
Transfer of cash advances from one accountable officer to another should be stopped.
Cash advances should be granted only to designated Disbursing Officers, and that elective officials be granted cash advances only for travelling expenses. Henceforth, granting of cash advances to the Municipal Mayor should be stopped.
The Municipal Accountant trace back transactions in prior years to determine the nature and the persons accountable for the cash advances amounting to ₱317,410.72 and demand the liquidation or return thereof.

We have have recommended the following:                                 >         Justify the noted lapses;
>   Utilize the LDRRMF for programs, projects and activities which conform to the objective of the fund;
>        Submit the necessary supporting documents to validate the distribution of goods to intended beneficiaries; and
>         Require the Sangguniang Bayan to pass a resolution for the opening of a special trust fund account for the unexpended balance of the fund

15.6	In view of the foregoing noted deficiencies, we have recommended that:
The 20% development fund should be appropriated and utilized for programs and projects that are considered capital or investment in nature;
Henceforth, management should strictly observe the pertinent provisions of DILG-DBM Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2011-1 dated April 13, 2011 on the appropriation and utilization of the 20% of the annual IRA for development projects to ensure that said fund is optimally utilized.

19.9	In view of the noted lapses, we have recommended the following:
The Municipal Mayor creates a GFPS Execom, TWG and Secretariat that will supervise, advocate and install a GAD Focal Point System (GFPS) as well as the required Gender Responsive Monitoring and Evaluation (M&E) System;
The Municipal Mayor with the help of the Sangguniang Bayan, formulate and adapt a Local GAD Code;
The MSWDO being the leading authority in identifying gender related issues and concerns, see to it that GAD activities are identified through the use of HGDG and that the GAD plan are regularly updated; and
Henceforth, management sees to it that said plan and budget are approved by the DILG and the PPDO.
